social_posts.post_text: In midst of applying for a grant which has me going through my archive of photos. It’s crazy to look back at all the work produced that I have forgotten about 👉

❄️C H E E R S !  Next Sunday I will be vending at a wonderful queer event, The Rhinestone Jetski Indoor Pleasure Cruise and  Holiday Market in the Icebox Project Space located in Crane Arts. The event is ticketed and runs from 12pm-5pm. I have a lot of new work I’m excited to share! Anything that I do not sell will immediately go up on my web-shop at 5:00pm following the market. Happy holidays!❄️
❄️🎾some loud colors for the market this sunday!🎾❄️
My first take on a new pedestal fruit bowl🍒🍓🍇🍎🍉🍑🍊🍋🍍🍌🥑🍏🍈🍐🥝🥭🥥
Round stackable bowls coming to the market and web-shop with me tomorrow!
New tissue box covers will be available at the holiday market today and what is left will be up on my webshop this evening at 5:00pm EST!

Exciting news! I’ve made my first piece of furniture with one of my oldest friends @stevensontaylorfurniture ! This is the Toow Side table which will hopefully be the first of many collaborative pieces between us (what we are calling Stone & Timber). The top portion of the table is made of Walnut and the bottom portion is a speckled white stoneware clay. This piece is available for purchase for Philadelphia local pick up or delivery as far as New York City (with an added transportation fee). If interested in purchasing please DM me for cost, dimensions, etc!
A large pedestal bubble bowl in cobalt blue & natural stoneware

As the year comes to an end I’m reflecting on everything 2022 contained. I built and launched my first webshop, lost my studio space, moved into a new studio, shipped more work than I ever have and navigated this business in the midst of a recession with intense inflation. 2022 tested me and left me with questions about doing this business right. Entering 2023 with tenacity and some big aspirations!
The last few steps to completing an order for the lovely owners of @forinphl for their new spot that is opening next month in our neighborhood! Can’t wait!💚

Hit the ground running in January! While I think it’s so important to share our successes I think it’s also crucial to share our failures and struggles, which is where we grow the most. Back in November of ‘22 I applied for my first ever grant. It was a nationwide call for teaching artists and there were close to 600 applicants but today I was informed that I was not one of the recipients. While I would have loved to receive it, I am grateful to have gone through the process, learned a ton and am very prepared to apply for even more in 2023.
The journey of creating a 40 piece dinner set for a customer!

It’s been a busy start to 2023 which has consisted of working a lot with Philly local businesses, cafes, restaurants and bars. It typically results in me making new work while getting to collaborate with other entrepreneurs which is always exciting and something I love. With that being said, I am working towards a new web-shop drop for early spring! Keep any eye out for dates!
Large serving pieces headed for my next webshop drop!
Gotta find someone who looks at me the way I look at my pots 😜
Trimming and finishing a Pedestal Bowl
💥This S A T U R D A Y, 3/25 @ 12pm EST, I will be doing a big webshop drop with all new work including these high walled plate/bowls in various forms & color ways!💥
🌸Cheers to Spring! Next webshop drop coming this Saturday, 3/25 @ 12:00pm EST. Have a range of these coupes available which are also great for desserts like Affogato!🌸
Large mugs coming to my webshop update this Saturday 3/25 at 12:00pm EST!
The aim of this drop of work is for my customers to be able to build a dinner set perfect for a special meal. Webshop update this Saturday, 3/25 @12:00pm EST
💛Turmeric yellow bowl/plate in 2 forms 👉
A variety of 🌱p l a n t e r s🌱 will be available on my webshop update today at 12:00pm EST!

💙Over the moon with gratitude from yesterday’s webshop update. Only two pieces are left which happen to be my favorite from this drop. This pedestal bowl is great for any amount of fruit or the perfect serving dish for a family style dinner💙

A goal for 2023 is to have my work living in and being used daily by various small businesses across the city, becoming part of the landscape of Philadelphia. Very excited about these tiki cups I made for @rd_philly new menu this season. Go get a delicious zombie cocktail that pairs perfectly with this cup! 🍍🍍🍍
The making of a 14” terracotta accordion planter!

I suddenly lost someone who was  very special and monumental to my life on Sunday, March 14th. It has been an honor to aid in remembering his life as well as create the most meaningful piece I ever have.

This has been the longest hiatus I’ve ever taken from making since I started this business. Grief has been a tricky thing for me to navigate so far after the experience of suddenly losing someone very close to me. For whatever reason, I have had a lot of anxiety about returning to the studio. Im hoping to find joy, reflection, and fulfillment now that I’m back in here to make.
A range of new pieces freshly unloaded from the glaze kiln today!
Back in a great groove in the studio finishing up a 30 piece dinner set for a customer.
Slinging pots on this lovely queer day thanks to @marthakensington !
A 30 piece matte white & lapis dinner set for a client 👉swipe through to see each piece
My first workshop! Swipe through to learn more about it as well as some answers to some questions that have come up!👉Hope to see you there! Link to tickets for the event can be found in my bio💕
Last weekend this pot met it’s demise in the kiln but she’s been remade better and stronger!
🍜 appreciation

I met Shannon (founder of @helloyowie ) 6 years ago when she asked me to make plates for a dinner event in her original retail space. Fast forward to today, she has become a mentor, neighbor, collaborator and forever friend. We cheer each-other on as we’ve grown our businesses and continue challenging ourselves to push our dreams to the next level. I’m so honored to have my first piece of furniture in YOWIE’s beautiful hotel and can’t wait to see where we are at 6 years from today.
My first clay workshop was wonderful! Everyone did an amazing job and the energy was 👌. I will be advertising my next workshop for September soon!
Process of throwing a new vase form !
👉Just posted tickets for my next workshop on Eventbrite! Link in bio!
Thinking about how my kiln still doesn’t work, l have tendinitis in my wrist, that my favorite Laguna clay is no more, AND how I’m still ready to scale my business to the next level🤪
New vases will be available in my late summer web-drop! Saturday, September 16th @ 12:00pm! 👉🤍💗💛

Various serving bowls coming to my webshop soon!

Jennifer is a long time friend, founder of @sway.at.home and an overall amazing, impressive person. She has been supporting and collecting my work for many years and was gracious enough to let me photograph my work living in her beautiful home. It’s truly an honor to be able to see years of work being put to good use in someone’s life 👉💕
Large bubble serving bowls in new color-ways coming to my webshop along with more new work this Sunday, October 22nd at 11am EST!👉

TBH, whether you’re hosting for a crowd or a #partyofone, these goodies will elevate any evening.

@amyrosethielen ~ Her cookbook, Company: The Radically Casual Art of Cooking for Others

Follow the link in bio to enter your email address! Giveaway closes at 11:59 p.m. ET on Wednesday, Nov. 8.

I’m very excited to showcase the big moves that I will be making this year.
